# Philodendron warszewiczii

*Philodendron serpens
}}
Philodendron warszewiczii is a species of flowering plant in the family Araceae. It is native to southern Mexico, and to Central America. A climber, it is typically found in the seasonally dry tropics at elevations from , where it can grow in soil, on rocks, or epiphytically on trees. It is facultatively deciduous in the dry season.
